Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Mushrooms{150%g}(roughly chopped).

Halve the @Chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(peaed and chopped into small pieces).

Stir the @Coconut Milk{1%pack} (or shake the packet) to dissolve any lumps.

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

When the pan is hot, add the onion, @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g} and mushrooms. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Fry until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Add the @Garlic, Ginger & Lemongrass Paste{1%sachet} and chilli (use less if you don't like spice).

Fry until fragrant, another ~{30%seconds}.

Add coconut milk and @Water{25%ml} (double for 4p) to the pan.

Cover and cook for ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if necessary. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

While the chicken cooks, trim and thinly slice the @Scallion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Add the @Honey{2%sachets} and @Miso Paste{1%sachet} to a #bowl{} and mix to combine.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.

Top with the fragrant chicken curry.

Drizzle the honey miso sauce over the chicken.

Finish with a sprinkling of sliced scallion.